Identified critical security gaps and missing Android-specific entries
Identified critical security gaps and missing Android-specific entries
The file is a decent starting point, but it has some notable issues and gaps for a public Android/Kotlin project. Here's a full breakdown:

🔴 Problems (fix these)
1. gradle.properties should NOT be ignored This file typically contains project-wide Gradle settings like org.gradle.jvmargs, android.useAndroidX=true, etc. Ignoring it will break the project for contributors. Only secrets should be kept out — and those should live in local.properties or a separate untracked file.

2. Missing keystore / signing config — SECURITY RISK For a public repo, you must ignore signing files. Add:

*.jks
*.keystore
keystore.properties
3. Hardcoded hprof filename java_pid3592.hprof is a one-time leftover file. Replace it with a wildcard:

*.hprof
🟡 Missing entries (recommended additions)
gitignore
# Android signing (IMPORTANT for public repos)
*.jks
*.keystore
keystore.properties

# Android Studio profiling
captures/
.navigation/

# CMake / NDK builds
.cxx/
*.so

# Kotlin build caches
*.hprof          # replaces the hardcoded java_pid3592.hprof

# Firebase (contains API keys — usually should be ignored)
google-services.json
✅ What's fine
local.properties ✔ (correctly ignored — contains SDK path)
build/, .gradle/, out/ ✔
*.apk, *.aab ✔
.idea/, *.iml ✔ (reasonable for public projects)
OS/editor noise (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db, .swp) ✔
Summary
Area	Status
gradle.properties ignored	🔴 Fix — breaks builds for contributors
Keystore/signing files	🔴 Missing — security risk
Hardcoded hprof filename	🟡 Replace with *.hprof
NDK/CMake artifacts	🟡 Missing
Core Android ignores	✅ Good
The most urgent fix is removing gradle.properties from the ignore list and adding keystore-related entries before making the repo public.

